{
  "doc_id": "2102",
  "text": "Although there have been several models of the enumeration process, not many of them have been implemented on a robot platform or robot simulator. In this field Ruciński et al. [CITATION_1] , using the iCub humanoid robot [CITATION_2] , developed a model capable of number comparison and parity judgement that took into account the SNARC (spatial-numerical association of response codes) effect. In another work [CITATION_3] they constructed a recurrent neural network that is first taught to recite the numbers in the counting order and then to count the presented objects with or without proprioceptive gesture input from iCub robot.",
